<p class="head"><span class="AddHand-editors">[18<sup>th</sup>]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[Aug]</span>ust Continued</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[t]</span>hat Carrying from Morning to night was nothing in <span class="AddHand-editors">[comp]</span>arison to Paddling through the mud, where they some tim<span class="AddHand-editors">[e]</span>s pulled for a Quarter of an Hour with all their might, without being able to gain the Length of the Canoe<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[I]</span> told them that the Only remedy was perseverance, and patience, so as to get out of it the Sooner, andeed, I must Own, that paddling through the Mud is Certainly the most fatigueing labour a Man Can meet with<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>e Came over five portages, and did not <span class="AddHand-author">make</span> Above 4 Leagues<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>e Camped at grand de Vaze, a portage 22 Acres long<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">19<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he Same Labour over Again<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>e are oblige to haul the Canoes through the Mud with tracking lines, when ever we Can get Nigh the Shore<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  One may drive a pole twenty feet long down to the End, in all these Muddy lakes and the Smallest Dog is not even Able to Swim in them<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>e came over 3 portages, 2 of them long Ones, and Camped at perche a Chavaudreuil<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">20<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[I]</span>t Rain'd the whole Day, but not so heavy as I wish'd, but still it Obliged us to lay bye<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he Men were so much fatigued, that they Employed the most part of the Day in Sleeping, but it was a long, and lonesome Day for</p>

